From 97d1ca391b17f27d3daff4241fe3010e1483e2d7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: jiviny <jivin25@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 14:31:08 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add daytona runtime

Implements the Daytona slot in the v1 runtime layer, mirroring the modal
runtime: DaytonaConfig in the RuntimeConfig union, sandbox provisioning via
the daytona SDK (resources mapped from Modal units, GPU spec split via
parse_gpu, inactivity auto-stop with delete-on-stop as the lifetime
backstop), creation pacing via creation_limiter (org-tier-aware default)
plus the shared _TUNNEL_LIMITER in expose(), exec with an in-band
stdout/stderr split (Daytona returns one combined stream), fs read/write
(the upload creates missing parents), nohup run_background, and a
cleanup/stop teardown pair keyed off the sandbox id so a stop cancelled
mid-delete is still cleaned by the atexit backstop.

public_url uses native preview links, signed on private sandboxes (the
default) so the colocated user-simulator path works without making ports
world-readable: the signed link needs no token header and is valid for
the sandbox's own lifetime (signing caps at 24h, the runtime's max).

Live-verified end to end (17/17): exit codes, stream split, env
passthrough, workdir, nested file IO, background processes, PEP 723 uv
scripts resolving deps in-sandbox, signed public_url serving sandbox
content to the host with no auth header (unsigned URL correctly rejected),
and server-side deletion after stop.
